Contextual Qualitative Math & CPU Operator v1.0

Overview

Classical mathematics excels at modeling quantitative phenomena—count, magnitude, ratio, and measurement.
However, much of reality operates in the qualitative domain: meaning, perception, context, value, and interpretation.

This document formalizes a bridge between these domains and proposes a next-generation mathematical primitive:

The Context–Perspective–Uncertainty Operator (CPU Operator)

⸻

Core Thesis

Mathematics is best understood as a:

Compression and manipulation language for structure

Progress in mathematics is driven not just by new discoveries, but by:
	•	better operators
	•	better representations
	•	lower ambiguity
	•	higher manipulability

⸻

